==English==

===Etymology===
Obscure. Panhandling always seems to involve a container for receiving loose change, so perhaps referring to a small, [[handled]] pan. This would seem to be the origin of the verb.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An urban [[begger]] who typically stands on a street with a outstretched container in hand, begging for loose change.
# A [[bum]].

[[vi:panhandler]]